member.name: F:Autodesk.Connectivity.WebServices.BOMSchm.InsepAsPrt
member.summary: Indicates whether assemblies with a BOMStructure of "Inseperable" should be treated as a single part in a PartsOnly scheme. When true, the inseparable assembly is treated as a single part and its children are ignored. When false, the children are included in the Parts Only view. In a “Structured” scheme, InsepAsPrt should always be set to "false".

member.name: F:Autodesk.Connectivity.WebServices.BOMSchm.InsepPrmtsPrch
member.summary: A value of true indicates that, in an assembly with a BOMStructure of "Inseperable", Components with a BOMStructure of "Purchased" are considered independent of the parent assembly. A value of false indicates that purchased children should be considered inseparable children of inseparable assemblies. In a "Structured" scheme, InsepPrmtsPrch should always be set to "false".
